name: aldehyde dehydrogenase (NAD+)
classes: Acting on the aldehyde or oxo group of donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: an aldehyde + NAD+ + H2O = a carboxylate + NADH + H+ [RN:R00538]
comment: Wide specificity, including oxidation of D-glucuronolactone to D-glucarate.

references.title: Aldehyde dehydrogenases.
references.journal: In: Boyer, P.D., Lardy, H. and Myrback, K. (Eds.), The Enzymes, 2nd ed., vol. 7, Academic Press, New York, 1963, p. 203-221.

references.title: Aldehyde dehydrogenase, a diphosphopyridine nucleotide-linked enzyme.
